  "text": "Statistical analysis was performed using SPSS Statistics 22 (IBM; Chicago, USA). Partial Spearman's rank correlation (control for age/gender) was used to evaluate the association amongst CAA-and AD-related parameters. Multinomial logistic regression (control for age/gender) was applied to compare Ab pathology groups for their association with CAA-and AD-related parameters, vascular risk factors, and alcohol abuse. Linear regression (control for age/gender) was used to determine the effect of B-CAA and B-Ab plaque stages on NIA-AA AD degree, CDR score, vascular risk factors, and alcohol abuse. B-Ab plaque stages and amyloid plaque loads used for statistical analysis were obtained from a previous publication in which the present cases were analyzed for the biochemical composition of Ab aggregates in plaques. [CITATION_1] ",
